16/04/2007
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- A local court sentenced Greek diplomat Constantine Bibikos to 21 years in prison Friday (April 13th) after convicting him of bribery. 
Bibikos, 40, Greece's ex-consul in Kiev, Ukraine, was found guilty of accepting bribes for issuing approximately 2,500 visas, as well as money laundering in early 2002. 
A former clerk at the Greek embassy in Kiev was sentenced to 19 years in prison, while an agent for a Ukrainian tour operator was sentenced in absentia to nine years. 
(Kathimerini, A1 TV - 14/04/07)
